<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM1.5.11">
<l>aṉṉamum mīṉuruvu māḷari yumkuṟaḷu</l>
<l rend="indent">māmaiyu māṉavaṉē yāyarkaḷ nāyakaṉē</l>
<l>yeṉava laṅkaḷaivā yāṭuka ceṅkīrai</l>
<l rend="indent">yēḻula kummuṭaiyā yāṭuka vāṭukeṉṟu</l>
<l>vaṉṉana ṭaimaṭavā ḷacōtai yukantaparicu</l>
<l rend="indent">vāṉapu kaḻpputuvaip paṭṭaṉu raittatami</l>
<l>ḻiṉṉicai mālaikaḷip pattumval lārulaki</l>
<l rend="indent">leṇṭicai yumpukaḻmik kiṉpama teytuvarē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who are skillful in [reciting] these ten sweet song garlands of Tamil [verse]</l>
<l rend="indent">that were spoken by the scholar of famed Putuvai</l>
<l>that are of a quality that is pleasing [like the words] of Yaśodā,</l>
<l rend="indent">the simple lady with the swan [like] gait, saying</l>
<l>“You who became the swan, the form of a fish, the man-lion, the dwarf, and the tortoise,</l>
<l rend="indent">O Leader of the cowherds, You who removes my suffering, please dance!</l>
<l>You who possesses the seven worlds, please dance the Ceṅkīrai, please dance!,”</l>
<l rend="indent">they will obtain great joy [and] the praise of the eight regions of the world.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
